Content Distribution Engine (CDE)

1. Purpose of This Document
This document defines the canonical data definitions (DATADEF) for the Content Distribution Engine (CDE).
It provides:
field-level semantic meaning
invariants and constraints
cross-engine contract expectations
authoritative reference for audits and integrations
This document complements NS-CDE-007 — DATAMODEL and completes the CDE documentation set.
2. DATADEF Principles
Semantic Stability — field meaning never changes
Immutability by Default — history is preserved via new records
Proof-Based Truth — delivery success requires evidence
Governed Mutation — high-impact changes require approval context
Cross-Engine Clarity — shared fields have single meaning
3. Content Artifact Definitions
3.1 content_artifact
Field
Definition
Notes
content_id
Canonical content identifier
Stable UUID
content_type
Content classification
listing / media / document / notification
source_engine
Originating engine
PIE / DRE / external
content_version
Version string
External or internal
created_at
Registration time (UTC)
Immutable
Invariants:
content_id never changes
content_version is opaque to CDE
4. Distribution Plan Definitions
4.1 distribution_plan
Field
Definition
Notes
plan_id
Distribution plan identifier
UUID
plan_version
Plan revision number
Integer
status
Lifecycle state
draft / submitted / approved / rejected / archived / cancelled
actor_id
Plan owner
IDN canonical
created_at
Creation timestamp
UTC
approved_at
Approval timestamp
Nullable
Invariants:
approved plans are immutable
revisions require new plan_version
