11. Cross-Engine Contract Expectations
Engine
CDE Contract
PIE
Provides content artifacts
DRE
Provides research artifacts
GGP
Governs plan approval
MUX
Executes channel adapters
SIG
Aggregates feedback signals
DAT
Consumes outcome metrics
IDN
Resolves actor/entity identity
CWP
Schedules and supervises execution
12. Validation & Constraints
all timestamps are UTC
all IDs are UUIDs
proofs required for success
idempotency keys enforced per attempt
13. Backward Compatibility Rules
fields may be added, never removed
field meaning never changes
deprecated fields remain readable
14. Document Position in CDE Corpus
This DATADEF completes the CDE documentation set (001–014).
It complements:
NS-CDE-007 — DATAMODEL
NS-CDE-006 — VERSION
